04:14.000 --> 04:15.000
Spent a career there.

04:15.000 --> 04:17.000
Retired as a sergeant major.

04:17.000 --> 04:19.000
Retired in 2020.

04:19.000 --> 04:23.000
And spent about 23 years working for the government.

04:23.000 --> 04:24.000
Deploying a lot.

04:24.000 --> 04:25.000
Jumping out airplanes.

04:25.000 --> 04:28.000
Doing interesting things in bad places, usually.

04:29.000 --> 04:32.000
After I retired, I started several companies.

04:32.000 --> 04:38.000
And some of my companies were contracted by the government to do different war game projects.

04:38.000 --> 04:44.000
At one of those war game events in 2021, we had an observation.

04:44.000 --> 04:47.000
It turned out to be class one UAPs.

04:47.000 --> 04:52.000
And we originally thought that that was a government-made, U.S. government-made tool.

04:52.000 --> 04:54.000
So, we were very secretive about it.

04:54.000 --> 05:01.000
We protected it and did all the due diligence to kind of make sure that that didn't get out anywhere, just in case it was made in America and need to be protected.

05:01.000 --> 05:03.000
So, that's how we kind of got into it.

05:03.000 --> 05:04.000
It was actually by accident.

05:04.000 --> 05:12.000
And I'd be remiss if I didn't mention, I am the, if you will, the lead operations guy.

05:12.000 --> 05:17.000
I'm the guy who drove the discovery, but I'm not the person, I'm not the pioneer that actually discovered it.

05:17.000 --> 05:18.000
Right?

05:18.000 --> 05:22.000
So, there's two pioneers in this field who wish to remain anonymous right now.

05:22.000 --> 05:25.000
One is Mr. K, I'll say.

05:25.000 --> 05:26.000
Okay.

05:26.000 --> 05:28.000
And he's a, he's a really cool dude.

05:28.000 --> 05:34.000
He's like a physicist, makes jet engines, flamethrowers, works on hot rods and does physics for fun as well.

05:34.000 --> 05:36.000
Like, he's really, really cool dude.

05:36.000 --> 05:41.000
