06:41.000 --> 06:44.000
And we are the little ants under the magnifying glass.

06:44.000 --> 06:47.000
We had a Class VII UAP.

06:47.000 --> 06:50.000
We went ahead and launched the helo to pursue it.

06:50.000 --> 06:54.000
Before the helo got here, it actually came and hovered right over us.

06:54.000 --> 06:57.000
For the first time, we saw a Class VII with a naked eye.

06:57.000 --> 06:58.000
It was very glinty.

06:58.000 --> 06:59.000
It looked metallic.

06:59.000 --> 07:02.000
Through our optics, we've always thought it was purple or black.

07:02.000 --> 07:06.000
Frankly, the reflections look like chrome almost color.

07:06.000 --> 07:11.000
So, you mentioned simulating war games and these UAPs show up.

07:11.000 --> 07:21.000
Do you think, and obviously you get into speculative territory and, you know, kind of philosophy, and I really want to get into kind of the hard data because that's what you guys sort of specialize in.

07:21.000 --> 07:29.000
But you think that might kind of show that we're living in some sort of three body problem universe or something where they don't want us to harm ourselves.

07:29.000 --> 07:36.000
You know, they show up around nuclear sites, they seem to, across the U.S., but even abroad as well.

07:36.000 --> 07:42.000
And does that signal that they don't want us to, you know, blow ourselves up or something?

07:42.000 --> 07:45.000
Or why do you think they show up around these sort of war games?

07:45.000 --> 07:49.000
So, we have some ideas on that, and I have some opinions on that.

07:49.000 --> 07:54.000
We'll say, for example, in 2021, the first time we saw them, we were running a war game for the government.

07:54.000 --> 07:59.000
The deliverable for the war game was tactics, and we had a blue team and a red team.

07:59.000 --> 08:08.000
The blue team's job was to bring American-made, government-made, and commercial-made protective systems for blue forces.

08:08.000 --> 08:11.000
Think air defense, think counter drone, think other things.

08:11.000 --> 08:20.000
And then the red team was, again, American-made as well as one-off hobbyist-type drones, aircraft, and other things.

08:20.000 --> 08:30.000
And the red team's job was to penetrate the airspace of the blue team or cause them to be able to basically tactically envelop the blue team and cause them to have a loss.

08:30.000 --> 08:33.000
And the blue team's job was to stop that.

08:33.000 --> 08:42.000
And so, we're running this event, and I'm up on the roof of a very tall building with two young interns with binoculars looking for drones, right?

08:42.000 --> 08:44.000
So, we're up there.

08:44.000 --> 08:49.000
I think we were two weeks into the project at this point, every day, 12 hours a day, running the war game.

08:49.000 --> 09:01.000
And we were looking for drones as the mission controller or project controller, if you will, so I can modulate launch now, don't launch now, or hey, blue team, did you guys even pick up on that drone that was just here?

09:01.000 --> 09:07.000
Like, so I'm trying to modulate the exercise and keep things flowing so we can be effective in developing tactics.

09:07.000 --> 09:11.000
And my camera operator, Mr. K, was like, hey, you have to come see this.

09:11.000 --> 09:13.000
There's something going on.

09:13.000 --> 09:21.000
So, understand, we're up on the roof, scanning the sky with binoculars, listening, seeing, and we see drones, but we don't see this other stuff.

09:21.000 --> 09:23.000
So, I go down to the truck, and he's like, look at this.

09:23.000 --> 09:28.000
And he shows me the class one formation of seven, the first sighting we had.

09:28.000 --> 09:31.000
This was the last day of the event, so we were shutting down a few hours later.

09:31.000 --> 09:33.000
And just for the audience, class one?

09:33.000 --> 09:34.000
Class one's the Tetra.

09:34.000 --> 09:35.000
Okay.

09:35.000 --> 09:37.000
So, it's a black-bodied object.

09:37.000 --> 09:39.000
It tumbles and spins at a very high rate of speed.

09:39.000 --> 09:42.000
We're shooting at about 26 frames per second, I believe.

09:42.000 --> 09:51.000
And between each frame, it's changed drastically in its flight characteristics and signature so that we can only see a little bit of it, and we can't really derive the shape.

09:51.000 --> 09:54.000
It looks like a tetrahedron, but it's really hard to say from the footage we have.

09:54.000 --> 10:05.000
It looks like a tetrahedron that is wearing a hat, and the hat looks like it's made out of atmosphere, as in if you have a low-pressure, high-pressure differential, you can get vapor.

10:05.000 --> 10:06.000
Mm-hmm.

10:06.000 --> 10:12.000
As in when a fast-moving jet breaks the speed of sound and you see a vapor on the wings.

10:12.000 --> 10:13.000
Mm-hmm.

10:13.000 --> 10:15.000
That same effect looks like what we're seeing around the class one.

10:15.000 --> 10:16.000
Mm-hmm.

10:16.000 --> 10:27.000
And it basically wears it like some kind of field is holding it in place, and it's kind of there around it, kind of hiding the black body from the observer, if you will.

10:27.000 --> 10:28.000
Interesting.

10:28.000 --> 10:30.000
And then that vapor tends to flash.

10:30.000 --> 10:31.000
Uh-huh.

10:31.000 --> 10:38.000
It catches, as it's moving kind of violently, it catches the sun's rays, I believe, and reflects back.

10:38.000 --> 10:47.000
So that was actually what he saw was he was looking in the sky for drones, thinking nothing about UFOs, UAPs, or anything else, and saw flashing and said, what is that?

10:47.000 --> 10:53.000
Zoomed in and be like, oh, wow, there's seven of these craft in a tight formation maneuvering on us.

10:53.000 --> 10:54.000
Right?

10:54.000 --> 10:58.000
And again, I told you I was on the roof with interns with good ears and good eyes better than mine.

10:58.000 --> 10:59.000
We're not seeing a thing.

10:59.000 --> 11:00.000
Yeah.

11:00.000 --> 11:07.000
