01:03:37.000 --> 01:03:43.000
So it moves from point to point instantaneously as it moves along a stable trajectory.

01:03:43.000 --> 01:03:49.000
And when I say stable trajectory, maybe it's, maybe it's flight path is 80 knots.

01:03:49.000 --> 01:03:50.000
Right.

01:03:50.000 --> 01:03:57.000
But on imagery and on radar, it is bouncing all over in a, perhaps like a, like a tube almost,

01:03:57.000 --> 01:03:58.000
almost like it's in the subway.

01:03:58.000 --> 01:04:01.000
And you took like the Tasmanian devil and threw him the subway and said, go downtown.

01:04:01.000 --> 01:04:06.000
He's going to bounce all over the subway while he moves down that, that tubular tunnel there.

01:04:06.000 --> 01:04:08.000
That's kind of what we're seeing in the sky.

01:04:08.000 --> 01:04:09.000
Interesting.

01:04:09.000 --> 01:04:14.000
So as the Tasmanian devil bounces all over the tunnel, he's still moving a certain speed,

01:04:14.000 --> 01:04:15.000
but point to point, he's all over the map.

01:04:15.000 --> 01:04:16.000
Yeah.

01:04:16.000 --> 01:04:17.000
Right.

01:04:17.000 --> 01:04:18.000
But within a constrained area.

01:04:18.000 --> 01:04:19.000
That's fast.

01:04:19.000 --> 01:04:25.000
So the, the class three, um, uh, we've never seen one up close.

01:04:25.000 --> 01:04:26.000
Yeah.

01:04:26.000 --> 01:04:30.000
We don't know why it vibrates and how it's vibrating, but for sure it is vibrating.

01:04:30.000 --> 01:04:33.000
Cause we have it on imagery and on radar showing it vibrating.

01:04:33.000 --> 01:04:39.000
Um, and, um, that does meet the threshold of several of the five characteristics or maybe

01:04:39.000 --> 01:04:40.000
six characteristics of UAPs.

01:04:40.000 --> 01:04:45.000
And that is instantaneous movement from point to point that again, there's no contrail.

01:04:45.000 --> 01:04:47.000
There's no visible propulsion.

01:04:47.000 --> 01:04:52.000
It's just moving, you know, and we've had to ask ourselves, and it's still a theory is,

01:04:52.000 --> 01:04:59.000
is everything in the sky, you know, a holographic projection is all just, just the government

01:04:59.000 --> 01:05:02.000
or a government messing with our heads, making us think we're seeing something.

01:05:02.000 --> 01:05:05.000
And all it is, is plasmoids from space based lasers.

01:05:05.000 --> 01:05:06.000
Right.

01:05:06.000 --> 01:05:10.000
Uh, making shapes and they're bouncing across the sky to, to throw us off or make us think

01:05:10.000 --> 01:05:11.000
a thing.

01:05:11.000 --> 01:05:14.000
Um, I accept that that could be a possibility.

01:05:14.000 --> 01:05:15.000
Right.

01:05:15.000 --> 01:05:19.000
Um, because what we're looking at with the class three defies any known physics, any known

01:05:19.000 --> 01:05:21.000
logic of how it's maneuvering.

01:05:21.000 --> 01:05:23.000
So is it really there?

01:05:23.000 --> 01:05:27.000
Is it, is it, like I said, a plasmoid with lasers or is there actually a physical craft

01:05:27.000 --> 01:05:30.000
there moving across the sky?

01:05:30.000 --> 01:05:34.000
They'd have to be, if the government were doing that, they'd have to know where you guys

01:05:34.000 --> 01:05:40.000
are and then like be trying to spoof you or something, which I guess is possible.

01:05:40.000 --> 01:05:42.000
But, uh, you know, I don't know.

01:05:42.000 --> 01:05:43.000
That's, that's fascinating.

01:05:43.000 --> 01:05:50.000
Um, do any of these classes, are they attributed more to the psionic assets calling them in

01:05:50.000 --> 01:05:52.000
versus the machine based?

01:05:52.000 --> 01:05:58.000
Like, is, is it like the case of just an example, the jellyfish only shows up with the machine

01:05:58.000 --> 01:06:03.000
based thing or the psionic asset only attracts, you know, this particular class.

01:06:03.000 --> 01:06:06.000
Is that, can you, can you do those sort of attributions?

01:06:06.000 --> 01:06:07.000
Do you have data against that?

01:06:07.000 --> 01:06:10.000
So we have four and a half years of data with no psionics involved at all.

01:06:10.000 --> 01:06:11.000
Wow.

01:06:11.000 --> 01:06:12.000
Right.

01:06:12.000 --> 01:06:13.000
So that was all machine based.

01:06:13.000 --> 01:06:14.000
Yeah.

01:06:14.000 --> 01:06:15.000
Yeah.

01:06:15.000 --> 01:06:16.000
We were running these government events.

01:06:16.000 --> 01:06:17.000
Nobody there was doing anything psionic.

01:06:17.000 --> 01:06:19.000
And if they did, they wouldn't have a clearance and they couldn't be there anyway.

01:06:19.000 --> 01:06:20.000
Right.

01:06:20.000 --> 01:06:23.000
Like the government probably wouldn't allow them to be present and I probably wouldn't have

01:06:23.000 --> 01:06:27.000
hired them onto my team to come help run the event if they were doing those things.

01:06:27.000 --> 01:06:32.000
Um, so no, um, four and a half years has no psionics whatsoever.

01:06:32.000 --> 01:06:33.000
Okay.

01:06:33.000 --> 01:06:35.000
We have eight classes with that.

01:06:35.000 --> 01:06:40.000
That said, once we started doing this, uh, in a very open mindset of, uh, while I'm not

01:06:40.000 --> 01:06:42.000
a believer, I'm completely open.

01:06:42.000 --> 01:06:47.000
Like I've described several obscure theories that could hold true, whether it's a holographic

01:06:47.000 --> 01:06:51.000
projection, whether it's off planet, on planet, all these different theories.

01:06:51.000 --> 01:06:54.000
We have to, like, I don't have to believe all of them, but I have to accept that they

01:06:54.000 --> 01:06:55.000
could be true.

01:06:55.000 --> 01:06:56.000
Yeah.

01:06:56.000 --> 01:06:59.000
I'm completely open-minded here to include on the psionic side.

01:06:59.000 --> 01:07:00.000
Yeah.

01:07:00.000 --> 01:07:05.000
And what I would offer is on the psionic side, I have had personal observations of things

01:07:05.000 --> 01:07:11.000
that the psionic team has done that appear to validate that their methods work.

01:07:11.000 --> 01:07:12.000
Yeah.

01:07:12.000 --> 01:07:20.000
One example is, um, uh, in August, uh, one of our principal psionic assets, Jordan, apparently

01:07:20.000 --> 01:07:23.000
called in a craft and it, it could be an egg.

01:07:23.000 --> 01:07:24.000
I don't know what it is.

01:07:24.000 --> 01:07:25.000
Mm-hmm.

01:07:25.000 --> 01:07:28.000
And he's wearing a covering on his face.

01:07:28.000 --> 01:07:30.000
He's under a patio.

01:07:30.000 --> 01:07:36.000
He came and see the sky, uh, where I'm looking now, looking at him and he's having these experiences.

01:07:36.000 --> 01:07:42.000
And then Fred Baker was out on the back patio watching the sky while he hears Jordan freaking

01:07:42.000 --> 01:07:45.000
out down there on the, beneath the porch down there.

01:07:45.000 --> 01:07:49.000
And, and Fred independently is like, Oh, there it is.

01:07:49.000 --> 01:07:53.000
Because Jordan said where to look in the sky and Fred looked and saw an object.

01:07:53.000 --> 01:07:54.000
Whoa.

01:07:54.000 --> 01:07:55.000
So we videoed it.

01:07:55.000 --> 01:07:56.000
We didn't have the, all of our equipment.

01:07:56.000 --> 01:07:57.000
It's very expensive to procure.

01:07:57.000 --> 01:07:58.000
Mm-hmm.

01:07:58.000 --> 01:08:00.000
So we had a rudimentary equipment at that event.

01:08:00.000 --> 01:08:03.000
And when we caught rudimentary observations, right?

01:08:03.000 --> 01:08:04.000
Mm-hmm.

01:08:04.000 --> 01:08:09.000
So, but Jordan called it out, literally said, this is where it's at in the sky.

01:08:09.000 --> 01:08:10.000
This is what's happening.

01:08:10.000 --> 01:08:11.000
Here it is.

01:08:11.000 --> 01:08:12.000
And there's some other things to go with that.

01:08:12.000 --> 01:08:16.000
But point being, okay, how does that, how do you reconcile that?

01:08:16.000 --> 01:08:17.000
Yeah.

01:08:17.000 --> 01:08:18.000
How do you reconcile the entire event?

01:08:18.000 --> 01:08:19.000
Yeah.

01:08:19.000 --> 01:08:20.000
Right.

01:08:20.000 --> 01:08:22.000
Fast forward to February.

01:08:22.000 --> 01:08:26.000
Well, we ran an event in January without, with the equipment, with, with no dog whistle.

01:08:26.000 --> 01:08:27.000
Mm-hmm.

01:08:27.000 --> 01:08:28.000
And we got zero results.

01:08:28.000 --> 01:08:29.000
Mm-hmm.

01:08:29.000 --> 01:08:30.000
Right.

01:08:30.000 --> 01:08:34.000
We've run events without the dog whistle, but the same technology and play.

01:08:34.000 --> 01:08:35.000
Mm-hmm.

01:08:35.000 --> 01:08:37.000
And we don't get UAPs during those times.

01:08:37.000 --> 01:08:38.000
Okay.

01:08:38.000 --> 01:08:39.000
It's only a very narrow part of the day.

01:08:39.000 --> 01:08:44.000
So in February, up till February, I'd never seen a UAP with a naked eye, ever.

01:08:44.000 --> 01:08:45.000
Yeah.

01:08:45.000 --> 01:08:46.000
Wow.

01:08:46.000 --> 01:08:47.000
Wow.

01:08:47.000 --> 01:08:48.000
Wow.

01:08:48.000 --> 01:08:49.000
And five years of doing it, it was always through a, through a sensor.

01:08:49.000 --> 01:08:50.000
Yep.

01:08:50.000 --> 01:08:55.000
Um, in February, we actually had the, for, for the first time, the dog whistle paired with

01:08:55.000 --> 01:08:56.000
psionic assets.

01:08:56.000 --> 01:08:57.000
Mm-hmm.

01:08:57.000 --> 01:09:02.000
And while we can't say definitively that the psionic assets were responsible for the results

01:09:02.000 --> 01:09:03.000
we got.

01:09:03.000 --> 01:09:04.000
Sure.

01:09:04.000 --> 01:09:06.000
For the first time, they approximately close enough to see them.

01:09:06.000 --> 01:09:07.000
Wow.

01:09:07.000 --> 01:09:08.000
They'd never done that before.

01:09:08.000 --> 01:09:09.000
Wow.

01:09:09.000 --> 01:09:10.000
Now there's too many variables, right?

01:09:10.000 --> 01:09:15.000
It's ad nauseum until we can say with, with some kind of scientific rigor that cause an

01:09:15.000 --> 01:09:16.000
effect or-

01:09:16.000 --> 01:09:17.000
Coalition causation.

01:09:17.000 --> 01:09:18.000
Yeah.

01:09:18.000 --> 01:09:19.000
Yeah.

01:09:19.000 --> 01:09:20.000
We also introduced more chaos.

01:09:20.000 --> 01:09:22.000
For four and a half years, we had no helicopter.

01:09:22.000 --> 01:09:23.000
I had no Jake Barber.

01:09:23.000 --> 01:09:25.000
I had nobody to fly me up and go look.

01:09:25.000 --> 01:09:26.000
Mm-hmm.

01:09:26.000 --> 01:09:30.000
And part of our frustration with the government was we were underfunded, uh, when we were funded

01:09:30.000 --> 01:09:31.000
by the government for these events.

01:09:31.000 --> 01:09:32.000
Mm-hmm.

01:09:32.000 --> 01:09:38.000
And even when we were funded explicitly by certain parties to go look at UAPs, we were still underfunded

01:09:38.000 --> 01:09:39.000
there.

01:09:39.000 --> 01:09:42.000
So we didn't have the capacity to go get a helicopter or find Jake and, and go fly up

01:09:42.000 --> 01:09:43.000
to them.

01:09:43.000 --> 01:09:45.000
And, and because we're not Skinwalker Ranch, we are mobile.

01:09:45.000 --> 01:09:46.000
We are nomadic.

01:09:46.000 --> 01:09:47.000
Mm-hmm.

01:09:47.000 --> 01:09:52.000
Um, and our end state is that we would like to make contact with or retrieve some of this

01:09:52.000 --> 01:09:53.000
material.

01:09:53.000 --> 01:09:54.000
Right?

01:09:54.000 --> 01:09:55.000
Mm-hmm.

01:09:55.000 --> 01:09:57.000
So you're not gonna do that by standing on the ground, watching it and being static.

01:09:57.000 --> 01:09:58.000
Mm-hmm.

01:09:58.000 --> 01:09:59.000
Right?

01:09:59.000 --> 01:10:00.000
So we want to fly to them and observe them.

01:10:00.000 --> 01:10:04.000
So we introduced the helicopter activity and that introduced more chaos into the event.

01:10:04.000 --> 01:10:05.000
Right?

01:10:05.000 --> 01:10:06.000
So there's too many variables to understand.

01:10:06.000 --> 01:10:07.000
Yeah.

01:10:07.000 --> 01:10:09.000
Cause and effect with that many variables being changed.

01:10:09.000 --> 01:10:10.000
Yep.

01:10:10.000 --> 01:10:11.000
Right?

01:10:11.000 --> 01:10:15.000
So, and one time when you were up in a helicopter, the helicopter was sort of frozen.

01:10:15.000 --> 01:10:17.000
Like it couldn't continue on.

01:10:17.000 --> 01:10:18.000
Is that, is that right?

01:10:18.000 --> 01:10:21.000
We sent the helo out to intercept the tic-tac.

01:10:21.000 --> 01:10:27.000
But the first attempt failed because our radar was being jammed by the class 7 jellyfish.

01:10:27.000 --> 01:10:30.000
Where did it, where were we in the sky the first time you saw that?

01:10:30.000 --> 01:10:35.000
That was when we were seven kilometers or so out to the northwest, 340 at that spot that

01:10:35.000 --> 01:10:36.000
we went to?

01:10:36.000 --> 01:10:39.000
Yeah, we kept trying to climb and we just, it wouldn't let us.

01:10:39.000 --> 01:10:45.000
That helicopter launched and about a half mile out, the helicopter stopped moving.

01:10:45.000 --> 01:10:50.000
Engines running, blades are turning, but it would not go forward.

01:10:50.000 --> 01:10:51.000
It would not go up.

01:10:51.000 --> 01:10:53.000
It would not go left or right.

01:10:53.000 --> 01:10:54.000
It was stuck there.

01:10:54.000 --> 01:10:57.000
So we've had several interactions with UAPs in the air.

01:10:57.000 --> 01:10:58.000
Mm-hmm.

01:10:58.000 --> 01:11:02.000
First, the most prominent UAP we see are the jellyfish, the class 7.

01:11:02.000 --> 01:11:03.000
Mm-hmm.

01:11:03.000 --> 01:11:05.000
When we chase them, they evade us.

01:11:05.000 --> 01:11:06.000
Mm-hmm.

01:11:06.000 --> 01:11:11.000
We have on video us flying towards the class 7 and it changing its flight path, going into

01:11:11.000 --> 01:11:14.000
the wind, going perpendicular to the wind, and then elevating away from us.

01:11:14.000 --> 01:11:17.000
You know, we're moving at 80 plus knots and a little bird.

01:11:17.000 --> 01:11:25.000
And watching the class 7s with video and with radar, we know it's airspeed and maybe it's

01:11:25.000 --> 01:11:26.000
30 or 40 knots.

01:11:26.000 --> 01:11:31.000
We should be able to air-to-air intercept that all day long, but they consistently outrun

01:11:31.000 --> 01:11:32.000
us and escape us.

01:11:32.000 --> 01:11:33.000
Mm-hmm.

01:11:33.000 --> 01:11:36.000
So we've had that interaction.

01:11:36.000 --> 01:11:41.000
And then yes, with the Tic Tac, I'll talk through kind of what happened with the Tic Tac

01:11:41.000 --> 01:11:43.000
because it's actually very interesting.

01:11:43.000 --> 01:11:50.000
We had observed the class 7s fly through our radar beam and approximate our team repeatedly

01:11:50.000 --> 01:11:52.000
over four or five days.

01:11:52.000 --> 01:11:55.000
I believe it was four days.

01:11:55.000 --> 01:11:59.000
On the fourth day, the class 7, it was actually very interesting.

01:11:59.000 --> 01:12:03.000
We had nobody up on the hill outside of the Tic Tac.

01:12:03.000 --> 01:12:04.000
It was a barren hilltop.

01:12:04.000 --> 01:12:06.000
The helicopter wasn't there.

01:12:06.000 --> 01:12:11.000
On the fourth day, the class 7 came and hovered over us for about five minutes.

01:12:11.000 --> 01:12:12.000
All right?

01:12:12.000 --> 01:12:20.000
Now, that's never happened before and it hovered at about 800 meters over us so we could see

01:12:20.000 --> 01:12:22.000
it with the naked eye for the first time.

01:12:22.000 --> 01:12:28.000
As soon as we started coming outside the talk to look at it and grabbing other cameras to

01:12:28.000 --> 01:12:30.000
try and image it, it started moving away.

01:12:30.000 --> 01:12:31.000
All right?

01:12:31.000 --> 01:12:39.000
Now, understand the class 7 has some kind of apparently inherent microwave energy that

01:12:39.000 --> 01:12:40.000
it's emitting.

01:12:40.000 --> 01:12:41.000
Right?

01:12:41.000 --> 01:12:46.000
And that energy interferes with our cabling between our systems, we believe.

01:12:46.000 --> 01:12:53.000
So, we've noticed in effect that when the class 7 is present, we lose connection to our sensors,

01:12:53.000 --> 01:12:56.000
the high-end sensors that we're removed it into.

01:12:56.000 --> 01:13:05.000
So, our primary sensor didn't collect on that class 7 while it was in hover or over us.

01:13:05.000 --> 01:13:09.000
Once it departed the area, our sensors turned back on and we were able to actually image

01:13:09.000 --> 01:13:10.000
it.

01:13:10.000 --> 01:13:12.000
And I would offer, we've never had that happen before.

01:13:12.000 --> 01:13:13.000
Ever.

01:13:13.000 --> 01:13:16.000
We never had one approximate and we never had our sensors go down.

01:13:16.000 --> 01:13:22.000
So, we have all, you know, hundreds of thousands of dollars of camera gear inside the talk.

01:13:22.000 --> 01:13:23.000
Right?

01:13:23.000 --> 01:13:28.000
And so, here's the team scrambling like our primary sensor just quit working.

01:13:28.000 --> 01:13:31.000
And now we're like, all right, let's grab the cameras and go image it.

01:13:31.000 --> 01:13:33.000
So, everyone's in a hurry trying to do that.

01:13:33.000 --> 01:13:39.000
And poor Rory is out there just shooting all these videos and taking photos like, oh, this

01:13:39.000 --> 01:13:41.000
is amazing and talking through it.

01:13:41.000 --> 01:13:44.000
And then we look at the camera and there's no SD card in it.

01:13:44.000 --> 01:13:47.000
And we realized, because they were our secondary systems, like we'd never seen one with these

01:13:47.000 --> 01:13:48.000
cameras.

01:13:48.000 --> 01:13:49.000
Right?

01:13:49.000 --> 01:13:51.000
They were there for emergency use and we hadn't prepped them.

01:13:51.000 --> 01:13:52.000
Right?

01:13:52.000 --> 01:13:57.000
So, sometimes through those errors, you know, they're costly, but you learn.

01:13:57.000 --> 01:13:58.000
Right?

01:13:58.000 --> 01:14:01.000
Now, we are prepared for our secondary systems to become primary in case they approximate

01:14:01.000 --> 01:14:02.000
again.

01:14:02.000 --> 01:14:03.000
But we had to learn that the hard way.

01:14:03.000 --> 01:14:04.000
Right?

01:14:04.000 --> 01:14:08.000
So, we've seen the class sevens fly through our airspace routinely and probe apparently

01:14:08.000 --> 01:14:11.000
our active systems, our emanating systems.

01:14:11.000 --> 01:14:16.000
And so, on the, each day it seemed to get more, I would say aggressive, but I don't know

01:14:16.000 --> 01:14:17.000
that it's aggressive.

01:14:17.000 --> 01:14:19.000
It just got more interesting.

01:14:19.000 --> 01:14:24.000
And so, maybe the first day it flies over, over top of what our radar bubble should be.

01:14:24.000 --> 01:14:29.000
And then maybe the next day it flies over top, maybe a little bit lower and then deviates.

01:14:29.000 --> 01:14:31.000
Maybe it's coming from the west and it heads north.

01:14:31.000 --> 01:14:34.000
And then, and then later in the day it comes in from the west and heads south.

01:14:34.000 --> 01:14:36.000
As in as measuring our radar beam.

01:14:36.000 --> 01:14:37.000
Yeah.

01:14:37.000 --> 01:14:39.000
So, that's the impression we got.

01:14:39.000 --> 01:14:45.000
And then for the first time in February, we saw two jellyfish fly together in the radar

01:14:45.000 --> 01:14:47.000
and they offset from us equally.

01:14:47.000 --> 01:14:51.000
So, six kilometers north and south of us and they flew right past us, right?

01:14:51.000 --> 01:14:52.000
Whoa.

01:14:52.000 --> 01:14:53.000
So, we're like, well, that's pretty cool.

01:14:53.000 --> 01:14:54.000
I've never seen them in pairs before.

01:14:54.000 --> 01:14:55.000
Yep.

01:14:55.000 --> 01:14:59.000
And they're obviously interested in us in the middle and they're putting themselves in

01:14:59.000 --> 01:15:00.000
beam of our systems.

01:15:00.000 --> 01:15:01.000
So, then.

01:15:01.000 --> 01:15:06.000
Do they resemble the jellyfish that Jeremy Corbell revealed a couple of years ago?

01:15:06.000 --> 01:15:07.000
No, not to us.

01:15:07.000 --> 01:15:10.000
That looks like a shriveled up version of what we have, right?

01:15:10.000 --> 01:15:15.000
I would say, you know, our jellyfish are about two to three meters across in the head.

01:15:15.000 --> 01:15:16.000
Yeah.

01:15:16.000 --> 01:15:18.000
I think they look like an aspirin pill.

01:15:18.000 --> 01:15:19.000
Yeah.

01:15:19.000 --> 01:15:20.000
I don't know.

01:15:20.000 --> 01:15:22.000
And the tentacles are about five meters long.

01:15:22.000 --> 01:15:27.000
And I think the tentacles in your case, if I'm visualizing it correctly, are a little more

01:15:27.000 --> 01:15:31.000
dynamically moving than the, if you look at the Jeremy Corbell thing, it's, I think it's

