I would offer in known history that has never happened.

01:42:56.620 --> 01:42:57.620
Right.

01:42:57.620 --> 01:43:00.620
And if has happened, it's in a closed program that nobody knows about.

01:43:00.620 --> 01:43:02.620
Well, well, according to Jake, it's happened.

01:43:02.620 --> 01:43:03.620
Well, yes.

01:43:03.620 --> 01:43:04.620
Yeah.

01:43:04.620 --> 01:43:05.620
So show me the money.

01:43:05.620 --> 01:43:06.620
Yeah.

01:43:06.620 --> 01:43:07.620
Yeah.

01:43:07.620 --> 01:43:08.620
Right.

01:43:08.620 --> 01:43:09.620
I'm open-minded.

01:43:09.620 --> 01:43:10.620
Yeah.

01:43:10.620 --> 01:43:11.620
I'm hopeful.

01:43:11.620 --> 01:43:12.620
I would love for that to happen.

01:43:12.620 --> 01:43:13.620
Yeah.

01:43:13.620 --> 01:43:14.620
That'd be wild.

01:43:14.620 --> 01:43:15.620
I have no idea.

01:43:15.620 --> 01:43:16.620
Yep.

01:43:16.620 --> 01:43:17.620
When I like it too, of course I would.

01:43:17.620 --> 01:43:23.620
Is, is that the one you're holding out hope for as far as some sort of retrieval of actual

01:43:23.620 --> 01:43:27.620
material or, or are there others that you feel might be able to, you know, you might

01:43:27.620 --> 01:43:29.620
be able to derive material from or?

01:43:29.620 --> 01:43:36.620
Any of these crafts appear to have material and technology that we don't understand.

01:43:36.620 --> 01:43:37.620
Mm-hmm.

01:43:37.620 --> 01:43:41.620
So if any of them were to land or crash, that would be very interesting.

01:43:41.620 --> 01:43:42.620
Mm-hmm.

01:43:42.620 --> 01:43:43.620
I can say-

01:43:43.620 --> 01:43:44.620
Some can be non-physical though.

01:43:44.620 --> 01:43:47.620
Some are, or some sort of plasma ball thing.

01:43:47.620 --> 01:43:48.620
Right.

01:43:48.620 --> 01:43:49.620
I accept that that could be the case.

01:43:49.620 --> 01:43:50.620
Yeah.

01:43:50.620 --> 01:43:51.620
Yeah.

01:43:51.620 --> 01:43:54.620
Some of them might be holograms or plasmoids or things that if they land, there's molten,

01:43:54.620 --> 01:43:57.620
the fan turns to, to, to glass or metal or whatever.

01:43:57.620 --> 01:43:58.620
Right.

01:43:58.620 --> 01:43:59.620
Sure.

01:43:59.620 --> 01:44:00.620
Yeah.

01:44:00.620 --> 01:44:01.620
Why not?

01:44:01.620 --> 01:44:04.620
Um, I believe we've seen four UAPs crash over the years.

01:44:04.620 --> 01:44:05.620
Mm-hmm.

01:44:05.620 --> 01:44:06.620
Um.

01:44:06.620 --> 01:44:07.620
Really?

01:44:07.620 --> 01:44:08.620
Yep.

01:44:08.620 --> 01:44:09.620
You've seen them crash?

01:44:09.620 --> 01:44:10.620
We believe.

01:44:10.620 --> 01:44:11.620
Wow.

01:44:11.620 --> 01:44:12.620
And I say believe for a lot of reasons.

01:44:12.620 --> 01:44:14.620
We've seen three class ones.

01:44:14.620 --> 01:44:20.620
Um, uh, when we were doing, you know, in 2023 when we did something special for the government,

01:44:20.620 --> 01:44:22.620
uh, the UAPs behaved differently.

01:44:22.620 --> 01:44:23.620
Mm-hmm.

01:44:23.620 --> 01:44:26.620
And, uh, we saw about 200 UAPs in a day.

01:44:26.620 --> 01:44:27.620
Yeah.

01:44:27.620 --> 01:44:30.620
And they were almost all class ones at the time.

01:44:30.620 --> 01:44:34.620
And they were actually coming, instead of just flying through our airspace, they were

01:44:34.620 --> 01:44:36.620
coming from directly over us as if from space.

01:44:36.620 --> 01:44:37.620
Mm-hmm.

01:44:37.620 --> 01:44:38.620
So, they would come straight down.

01:44:38.620 --> 01:44:39.620
Mm-hmm.

01:44:39.620 --> 01:44:44.620
Ingress, and then, and then they would egress out low level away from us.

01:44:44.620 --> 01:44:46.620
And they did it in ones and twos and threes in time.

01:44:46.620 --> 01:44:47.620
Mm-hmm.

01:44:47.620 --> 01:44:49.620
We saw about 200 of them total, 240.

01:44:49.620 --> 01:44:50.620
Mm-hmm.

01:44:50.620 --> 01:44:53.620
Um, the class ones that are doing that, that's different.

01:44:53.620 --> 01:44:54.620
Mm-hmm.

01:44:54.620 --> 01:44:55.620
Right?

01:44:55.620 --> 01:44:59.620
So, as they were doing that, we saw three of them that, instead of coming in and the

01:44:59.620 --> 01:45:03.620
low level egressing, came in at an angle from directly overhead and just continued as

01:45:03.620 --> 01:45:04.620
if to the ground.

01:45:04.620 --> 01:45:05.620
Whoa.

01:45:05.620 --> 01:45:08.620
And they went below the ridge lines.

01:45:08.620 --> 01:45:09.620
Mm-hmm.

01:45:09.620 --> 01:45:11.620
And we never saw them come up.

01:45:11.620 --> 01:45:12.620
Did you go look for them?

01:45:12.620 --> 01:45:13.620
Yeah.

01:45:13.620 --> 01:45:16.620
So, it was actually really bad timing.

01:45:16.620 --> 01:45:21.620
Um, that year we had a really epic rainfall.

01:45:21.620 --> 01:45:22.620
Mm-hmm.

01:45:22.620 --> 01:45:26.620
That afternoon, after the show was over, it rained for like two days straight.

01:45:26.620 --> 01:45:27.620
Oh, man.

01:45:27.620 --> 01:45:28.620
Um, I had to wait about a week.

01:45:28.620 --> 01:45:29.620
Mm-hmm.

01:45:29.620 --> 01:45:34.620
And then I took a whole crew, um, for a, uh, hunt for a cartel drone that had crashed.

01:45:34.620 --> 01:45:35.620
Uh-huh.

01:45:35.620 --> 01:45:37.620
And we were out there looking for probably six or eight hours.

01:45:37.620 --> 01:45:38.620
We found nothing.

01:45:38.620 --> 01:45:39.620
And again, what are we looking for?

01:45:39.620 --> 01:45:41.620
I'm looking for a glass crystal ball.

01:45:41.620 --> 01:45:42.620
Sure.

01:45:42.620 --> 01:45:43.620
I'm looking for a cube.

01:45:43.620 --> 01:45:44.620
I'm not looking for a carcass.

01:45:44.620 --> 01:45:45.620
Yeah.

01:45:45.620 --> 01:45:46.620
Like, what am I looking, a tetrahedra?

01:45:46.620 --> 01:45:47.620
Like, what am I looking for right here?

01:45:47.620 --> 01:45:48.620
Yeah.

01:45:48.620 --> 01:45:49.620
Yeah.

01:45:49.620 --> 01:45:50.620
No idea.

01:45:50.620 --> 01:45:51.620
Yeah.

01:45:51.620 --> 01:45:52.620
Um, and, and some of these deserts are extremely rugged.

01:45:52.620 --> 01:45:53.620
And at the time, I didn't have a helicopter.

01:45:53.620 --> 01:45:54.620
Yep.

01:45:54.620 --> 01:46:04.620
Um, and then in 2024, um, we saw a class eight that started 3,500 meters above us as it came

01:46:04.620 --> 01:46:05.620
through in its sortie.

01:46:05.620 --> 01:46:06.620
This is the Hornet.

01:46:06.620 --> 01:46:07.620
Yep.

01:46:07.620 --> 01:46:10.620
And then finished at sortie just a couple hundred meters over the ground.

01:46:10.620 --> 01:46:12.620
Again, right at terrain level.

01:46:12.620 --> 01:46:13.620
Whoa.

01:46:13.620 --> 01:46:20.620
So, um, we went out this January and flew for probably two hours, hour looking for anything.

01:46:20.620 --> 01:46:21.620
Again, what are we looking for?

01:46:21.620 --> 01:46:22.620
I don't know.

01:46:22.620 --> 01:46:24.620
Extremely rugged and difficult terrain.

01:46:24.620 --> 01:46:27.620
So we think we've seen them crash without us, to our knowledge, doing anything to cause

01:46:27.620 --> 01:46:28.620
that.

01:46:28.620 --> 01:46:32.620
But we have yet to find any wreckage or find anything to show like, there is something

01:46:32.620 --> 01:46:33.620
here.

01:46:33.620 --> 01:46:34.620
So fascinating.

01:46:34.620 --> 01:46:35.620
Do you, what do you think?

01:46:35.620 --> 01:46:38.620
Sorry, I keep saying it so bad, but it is just like, it's just so interesting.

01:46:38.620 --> 01:46:43.620
Um, um, do you think that the government could be red teaming you guys at all?

01:46:43.620 --> 01:46:50.620
I mean, you know, uh, uh, you were in California near Palmdale and then you were also in Finley

01:46:50.620 --> 01:46:56.620
in Texas and those are near, you know, pretty sensitive training facilities, test sites, that

01:46:56.620 --> 01:46:57.620
sort of thing.

01:46:57.620 --> 01:47:03.620
Do you think that any of the primary space contractors are throwing stuff at you to kind

01:47:03.620 --> 01:47:08.620
of mess with your reconnaissance systems or mess with your detection systems or?

01:47:08.620 --> 01:47:11.620
So I would offer, my opinion is no.

01:47:11.620 --> 01:47:18.620
And the reason why is the craft we are seeing are conducting explicitly illegal operations

01:47:18.620 --> 01:47:19.620
of the guys.

01:47:19.620 --> 01:47:20.620
They're invisible.

01:47:20.620 --> 01:47:21.620
There's no markers.

01:47:21.620 --> 01:47:23.620
They don't have ADS-B.

01:47:23.620 --> 01:47:24.620
They don't have AIS.

01:47:24.620 --> 01:47:28.620
They don't have anything on board to show their presence.

01:47:28.620 --> 01:47:29.620
Mm-hmm.

01:47:29.620 --> 01:47:33.620
Also, they're flying adjacent to or in commercial air corridors.

01:47:33.620 --> 01:47:34.620
Mm-hmm.

01:47:34.620 --> 01:47:35.620
Right?

01:47:35.620 --> 01:47:36.620
Where all our commercial traffic flies.

01:47:36.620 --> 01:47:37.620
And they're flying at flight levels.

01:47:37.620 --> 01:47:38.620
We see them at flight level 180.

01:47:38.620 --> 01:47:41.620
We see them, I presume, higher than 180.

01:47:41.620 --> 01:47:45.620
We know higher, but we can't measure it because it's too high for a radar to reach.

01:47:45.620 --> 01:47:51.620
So, um, whoever is doing this, if it is domestic, like, they need to be, they need to, you

01:47:51.620 --> 01:47:54.620
know, get their affairs in order before they get caught.

01:47:54.620 --> 01:47:57.620
Because, um, if it is domestic, then they're breaking the law, frankly.

01:47:57.620 --> 01:47:58.620
Mm-hmm.

01:47:58.620 --> 01:47:59.620
Mm-hmm.

01:47:59.620 --> 01:48:00.620
You know, feloniously.

01:48:00.620 --> 01:48:01.620
Mm-hmm.

01:48:01.620 --> 01:48:02.620
Mm-hmm.

01:48:02.620 --> 01:48:06.620
Would you have a, say, a Mick West, we just talked about debunkers, Mick West or somebody

01:48:06.620 --> 01:48:11.620
like that out on the range to try to stress test, you know, what you're doing?

01:48:11.620 --> 01:48:12.620
Yeah.

01:48:12.620 --> 01:48:15.620
Um, I think we're willing to work with certain people.

01:48:15.620 --> 01:48:18.620
Um, frankly, personally, like, I have no time for debunkers.

01:48:18.620 --> 01:48:19.620
Yeah.

01:48:19.620 --> 01:48:21.620
Instead of saying I want to debunk, I just kind of get angry and kind of want to, like,

01:48:21.620 --> 01:48:22.620
lash out.

01:48:22.620 --> 01:48:23.620
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

01:48:23.620 --> 01:48:24.620
Like, just be open-minded.

01:48:24.620 --> 01:48:25.620
Yeah.

01:48:25.620 --> 01:48:26.620
Just listen.

01:48:26.620 --> 01:48:27.620
Take off your lenses.

01:48:27.620 --> 01:48:28.620
Yeah.

01:48:28.620 --> 01:48:30.620
Opinions and just open your mind and accept.

01:48:30.620 --> 01:48:31.620
Yeah.

01:48:31.620 --> 01:48:34.620
Uh, let us, let us give you, share some knowledge so we can learn together.

01:48:34.620 --> 01:48:37.620
Uh, should we, should we invite out a Mick West or whatever?

01:48:37.620 --> 01:48:38.620
Maybe that could happen.

01:48:38.620 --> 01:48:39.620
Yeah.

01:48:39.620 --> 01:48:41.620
Um, but frankly, like, I have no interest in him.

01:48:41.620 --> 01:48:47.620
But you would take a credentialed scientist out there who doesn't necessarily have a, you

01:48:47.620 --> 01:48:49.620
know, an a priori interest in UFOs.

01:48:49.620 --> 01:48:50.620
Yeah, absolutely.

01:48:50.620 --> 01:48:51.620
Okay.

01:48:51.620 --> 01:48:52.620
Okay.

01:48:52.620 --> 01:48:53.620
Because understand the difference.

01:48:53.620 --> 01:48:54.620
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

01:48:54.620 --> 01:48:55.620
I know the difference.

01:48:55.620 --> 01:49:00.620
One entity is hostile and extremely opinionated and has a preconceived notion of what you're

01:49:00.620 --> 01:49:04.620
saying and the other entity is open-minded and willing to understand what you're saying

01:49:04.620 --> 01:49:05.620
before they formulate their opinion.

01:49:05.620 --> 01:49:06.620
For sure.

01:49:06.620 --> 01:49:12.620
And so the one, uh, the hostile one, like, again, it, uh, I treat hostility with hostility.

01:49:12.620 --> 01:49:17.620
I have no desire to work with, talk to, interact, or face with them because bad things will happen

01:49:17.620 --> 01:49:18.620
and it's bad for everybody.

01:49:18.620 --> 01:49:19.620
Yeah.

01:49:19.620 --> 01:49:20.620
Right?

